  "description": "Sustained command selection with bistable state holding and directional modulation (Damasio fix). 2-state machine: forward and backward commands are each a 3-CH bistable ring (a=0,c=-65,d=0). RS triggers receive sensory input and drive cross-kill FS neurons. RS integrator #10 (modulator_fwd_in) feeds ONLY the forward ring. RS integrator #11 (modulator_bwd_in) feeds ONLY the backward ring. This makes emotion a directional value signal (somatic marker) not a symmetric gain knob. STDP plastic inputs to integrators learn from both rings (observe everything, act directionally).",
